places called Elton (Berkshire, Cheshire, Derbyshire, Durham, Herefordshire, Huntingdonshire, Lancashire, and Nottinghamshire). The Eltons in Chesire, Derbyshire, and Durham are from Old English <i>ǣl</i> ‘eel’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’. Elton in Berkshire is from the Old English female personal name <i>Æthelflǣd</i> (composed of the elements <i>æthel</i> ‘noble’ + <i>flǣd</i> ‘beauty’). Both Elton in Herefordshire and in Nottinghamshire are from the Old English personal name <i>Ella</i> + <i>tūn</i>. The Berkshire origin for the surname is especially well represented.","Norwegian: habitational name from a farm name in eastern Norway, in Old Norse <i>Elgjartún</i> ‘enclosed sacred place’ (or fenced in for <i>elg</i> ‘moose’?)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":55,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":64,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":99,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Elton was born in 1160, in England as the son of Elton. He had at least 1 son with Alice Younge."},"et":{"1160–":"1160–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1164–Female":"1164–Surnud","1198–1246":"1198–1246","–Male":"Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1160–":"1160–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1164–Female":"1164–Kuollut","1198–1246":"1198–1246","–Male":"Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1160–":"1160–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1164–Female":"1164–Décédée","1198–1246":"1198–1246","–Male":"Décédé","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Elton est né en 1160, à Angleterre, fils d’Elton. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Alice Younge."},"de":{"1160–":"1160–Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Verstorben","1164–Female":"1164–Verstorben","1198–1246":"1198–1246","–Male":"Verstorben","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Thomas Elton wurde 1160 in England, als Sohn von Elton geboren. Er hatte mit Alice Younge 